#Download UnrealEngine ZIP
1. Move to 'UnrealEngine.com'
2. Click 'Get Started Now' button
3. Fill the 'Join the Community' form and click 'Sign Up'
4. Move to 'GitHub.com' and Sign in
5. Back to 'UnrealEngine.com' and click 'Connected Accounts'
6. You can see 'GITHUB' icon and click it
7. To authorize connect, click 'Authorize EpicGames'
8. Move to 'https://github.com/EpicGames/UnrealEngine' and click 'Clone or download'

#Build UE4 in Linux
1. cd ~/Downloads/UnrealEngine-release/
2. ./Setup.sh
3. ./GenerateProjectFiles.sh
4. make SlateViewer
5. make ShaderCompileWorker UnrealLightmass UnrealPak UE4Editor

#Run UE4 in Linux
1. cd ~/Downloads/UnrealEngine/Engine/Binareis/Linux/
2. ./UE4Editor
3. Make a New Project
